 :power cycle: vt. (also, `cycle power' or just `cycle') To power off a
machine and then power it on immediately, with the intention of clearing some
kind of {hung} or {gronk}ed state. Syn. {120 reset}; see also {Big Red
Switch}. Compare {Vulcan nerve pinch}, {bounce} (sense 4), and {boot}, and
see the "{Some AI Koans}" (in Appendix A) about Tom Knight and the novice.